Backend end-to-end tests that drive a real HTTP server are intentionally omitted.
Integration tests in `tests/integration/` use `httpx.AsyncClient` with the FastAPI
`TestClient` transport — this covers the full request path (routes → services → DB)
without the flakiness and cost of managing a live server process. If full HTTP e2e
coverage is needed later, add it at the CI/infrastructure level (e.g., via Playwright
API testing or a dedicated contract-test suite), not inside the backend test tree.

