## MCP Servers

MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers provide tools that agents can invoke. Configured
in `.vscode/mcp.json`.

| Server | Type | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| **Context7** | stdio (bunx) | Up-to-date library/framework documentation |
| **GitHub** | http | GitHub issues, pull requests, repos, and code search |{% if use_playwright %}
| **Playwright** | stdio (bunx) | Browser automation for E2E web testing |{% endif %}{% if cloud_provider == 'azure' %}
| **Azure** | http | Azure resource management, deployments, monitoring |{% endif %}
| **Microsoft Docs** | http | Official Microsoft and Azure documentation |

### Usage

Agents with `context7/*` tools can resolve library IDs and fetch docs:
```
@Implementer Use context7 to look up the latest FastAPI dependency injection patterns
```

The GitHub MCP server provides repository context:
```
@Coordinator List open issues labelled "bug" in this repo
```

