## GSD-2

[GSD-2](https://github.com/gsd-build/GSD-2) is a TypeScript CLI coding agent built
on Pi SDK. It uses a state machine driven by files in `.gsd/` for
auto-mode sessions, context pre-loading, git isolation, and crash recovery.

### Configuration

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `.gsd/preferences.md` | Project conventions, verification commands, model preferences |
| `.gsd/mcp.json` | MCP server configuration for GSD sessions |
| `agent-instructions.md` | Root-level instructions picked up by GSD |

### Requirements

- Node.js ≥ 22.0.0 or Bun ≥ 1.0
- Install: `bun install -g gsd-pi@latest` (or `npm install -g gsd-pi@latest`)

### Usage

```bash
gsd                    # Interactive mode
gsd auto               # Auto mode (fresh session per task)
gsd "fix the login bug" # Direct task
```

### Bundled Agents

GSD includes three built-in agents: **Scout** (reconnaissance), **Researcher**
(deep analysis), and **Worker** (implementation). These complement the GitHub Copilot
agents in `.github/agents/`.
